  "source_id": "epilepsy",
  "name": "Epilepsy - Comprehensive Provider Query (DX + Meds + Procedures)",
  "description": "Simulates a neurologist identifying their complete epilepsy patient population. Combines: epilepsy diagnosis codes (multiple subtypes), AEDs, and EEG procedures. Tests Condition + MedicationRequest + Procedure resource union.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete epilepsy patient population for a quality improvement initiative on AED adherence and follow-up. From clinical experience, epilepsy patients are documented in different ways: most have a formal epilepsy diagnosis (parent epilepsy, generalized, seizure disorder, status epilepticus), most are on AEDs (phenytoin, carbamazepine, levetiracetam, valproate, lamotrigine), and most have undergone EEG for diagnosis or surveillance.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any epilepsy diagnosis\n2. Patients prescribed AEDs (phenytoin, carbamazepine, levetiracetam, valproate, lamotrigine)\n3. Patients who have undergone EEG\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found.",
